"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012398","Home Office","false","2018-11-27","<p>Each case is being looked at on its merits and we will consider any compensation where appropriate. We will be contacting the 19 applicants from who we need further information with a view to resolving their cases by the end of December. This timescale will depend on how quickly the further information is provided.</p><p>The review considered 1,697 cases which were refused under paragraph 322(5) on grounds relating to their character and conduct. We are not claiming these applicants are a threat to national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","194750 ; 194752","2018-11-27T17:26:25.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012398/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012398/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Skilled Workers: Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans he has to pay compensation to people who were wrongly refused Tier 1 general visas on the basis of rule 322(5) of the immigration rules; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","194749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012399","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-27","<p>We are concerned by reports of civilian casualties and displacement resulting from recent Taliban attacks in districts predominantly populated by Hazaras. We continue to monitor the situation closely, especially in Ghazni and Uruzgan districts. We understand that the Afghan National Defence and Security Forces are working to stabilise the security situation in both provinces.</p><p>The British Government continues to urge all parties to the conflict in Afghanistan to respect International Humanitarian Law, protect the civilian population and facilitate the provision of assistance by neutral and impartial humanitarian agencies. We urge the Government of Afghanistan to protect the rights of all ethnic and religious groups, including the Hazaras, in line with the Afghan constitution.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-27T13:52:11.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012399/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012399/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Afghanistan: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the validity of reports of recent killings of Hazara people by the Taliban in Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012400","Home Office","false","2018-11-27","<p>Each case is being looked at on its merits and we will consider any compensation where appropriate. We will be contacting the 19 applicants from who we need further information with a view to resolving their cases by the end of December. This timescale will depend on how quickly the further information is provided.</p><p>The review considered 1,697 cases which were refused under paragraph 322(5) on grounds relating to their character and conduct. We are not claiming these applicants are a threat to national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","194749 ; 194752","2018-11-27T17:26:25.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012400/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012400/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Skilled Workers: Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will update the House when his Department has made a decision on the 19 cases for which it is seeking more information from applicants before reconsidering their cases, as set out in the Review of Tier 1 (General) settlement refusals published on 22 November.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","194750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012401","Home Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>Border Force does not routinely publish this level of data on clandestines.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","194755","2018-11-30T12:52:16.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012401/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012401/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Undocumented Migrants: English Channel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the proportion of illegal migrants that have entered the UK via sea are (a) male, (b) female and (c) children.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","194751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012402","Home Office","false","2018-11-27","<p>Each case is being looked at on its merits and we will consider any compensation where appropriate. We will be contacting the 19 applicants from who we need further information with a view to resolving their cases by the end of December. This timescale will depend on how quickly the further information is provided.</p><p>The review considered 1,697 cases which were refused under paragraph 322(5) on grounds relating to their character and conduct. We are not claiming these applicants are a threat to national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","194749 ; 194750","2018-11-27T17:26:25.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012402/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012402/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Skilled Workers: Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the Tier 1 (general) visa applications refused under paragraph 322(5) of the immigration rules were refused on the basis of (a) criminality or threats to national security and (b) the applicant's character and conduct meaning that it is undesirable for them to remain in the UK.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","194752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012403","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-29","<p>No specific assessment has been made.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-11-29T14:13:02.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012403/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012403/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-22","Palliative Care: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of developing a competency framework for the provision of children’s palliative care.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012404","Treasury","false","2018-11-28","<p>On 1 April 2014, regulation of the consumer credit market, including the power to cap the cost of all forms of credit, was transferred to the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA).</p><p> </p><p>We have passed the Honourable Gentleman’s question on to the FCA, who will reply directly by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-11-28T13:05:54.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012404/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012404/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-11-22","Credit: Interest Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the cap on interest and charges relating to payday lending to (a) credit cards and (b) overdrafts.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012405","Treasury","false","2018-11-28","<p>On 1 April 2014, regulation of the consumer credit market, including payday lenders, was transferred to the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA).</p><p> </p><p>The Government legislated to require the FCA to introduce a cap on the cost of payday loans, which came into force on 2 January 2015. The FCA published a feedback statement in July 2017, showing that the price cap has been effective, leading to savings of approximately £150 million for 760,000 individuals using payday loans each year.</p><p> </p><p>The Government does not hold data on the number of public sector workers using payday loans companies.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-11-28T13:07:27.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012405/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012405/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-11-22","Credit: Interest Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of public sector workers using payday loan companies.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012406","Department for Education","false","2018-11-27","<p>The Department is allocating an additional £400 million of capital funding to schools in 2018–19. This funding is in addition to the £1.4 billion of condition allocations already provided this year to those responsible for maintaining school buildings. This will ensure that the school estate is well maintained.</p><p>As with Devolved Formula Capital, pupil referral units, alternative-provision academies, alternative-provision free schools, and general hospital schools will benefit from the funding, along with maintained nursery, primary and secondary schools, academies and free schools, special schools, non-maintained special schools and sixth-form colleges. It will also be allocated to those specialist post-16 institutions that have eligible state-funded pupils.</p><p>In December, the Department plans to publish a ready reckoner, which is a self-service calculation tool that will allow schools to estimate their allocations. The final allocations are expected to be published in the new year.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-11-27T16:08:34.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012406/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012406/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-11-22","Alternative Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether providers of alternative education will benefit from the £400 million capital bonus for schools, announced in Budget 2018.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","194753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012407","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-27","<p>On 22 November the Government’s response to the Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy (CWIS): safety review call for evidence was published. The response sets out a vision and a two year plan of action to help deliver the Government’s commitment to increasing cycling and walking and making our roads safer for vulnerable road users, including cyclists, pedestrians and horse riders. Among the key measures in the action plan, the Government has committed to reviewing the guidance in the Highway Code to improve safety for vulnerable road users.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the forthcoming refreshed Road Safety Statement will focus on four priority user groups including young road users, motorcyclists, older road users and rural road users.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-11-27T14:40:24.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012407/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012407/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-22","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to increase driver awareness of the dangers facing (a) cyclists, (b) motorcyclists and (c) other vulnerable road users.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012408","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-30","<p>The Department for Transport is supporting the Department for International Development as it leads the UK Voluntary National Review of progress towards the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-11-30T10:30:46.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012408/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012408/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-22","Department for Transport: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department plans to participate in the UK Voluntary National Review of Progress towards the sustainable development goals.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012409","Department for International Development","false","2018-11-28","<p>The Secretary of State for International Development, Rt Hon Penny Mordaunt, has not recently met with the Secretary of State for Transport to discuss the reduction of road fatalities across the world. However senior officials are working together across Departments as road safety is an identified shared priority.</p><p> </p><p>This year the Department for International Development extended its £4.5m funding to the Global Road Safety Facility (GRSF) with an additional £5.2m. We work closely with Department for Transport and Department for Health and Social Care (DHSC) on this issue with DHSC matching our funding to GRSF.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-11-28T15:03:03.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012409/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012409/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-11-22","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on reducing road fatalities across the world.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","194585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012410","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>​​Following the court hearing on Wednesday 21 November, the Foreign Secretary released a statement and discussed Matthew Hedges' case with Foreign Minister Abdullah bin Zayed and the United Arab Emirates Ambassador to the UK. I have also spoken to Deputy Foreign Minister Anwar Gargash, most recently on 23 November. We welcome the news of Mr Hedges' pardon. He has now returned to the UK and has reunited with his wife</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:09:52.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012410/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012410/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the authorities in the United Arab Emirates as a result of the sentencing of UK student Matthew Hedges.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012411","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>We welcome the news of Mr Hedges' pardon. He has now returned to the UK and has reunited with his wife.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:10:52.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012411/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012411/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government has taken to ascertain the (a) whereabouts and (b) health and well-being of Matthew Hedges following his sentencing.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012412","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>The Foreign Secretary personally raised this issue with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Zayed during his visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) on 12 November. The Foreign Secretary raised the issue several times with the UAE’s Foreign Minister, Abdullah bin Zayed, and most recently on 12 November. We have been clear that we do not agree with the charges but we are grateful to the UAE Government for resolving the issue.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:12:33.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012412/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012412/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assurances the Government received from the United Arab Emirates authorities on Matthew Hedges prior to his conviction and sentencing.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012413","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>As the Foreign Secretary has said, we have seen no evidence to suggest that there is any truth to these charges.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:14:14.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012413/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012413/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what evidence the UK Government has received from the United Arab Emirates authorities or other sources to support Matthew Hedges’s conviction.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012414","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>Following the court hearing on Wednesday 21 November, the Foreign Secretary released a statement and discussed Matthew Hedges' case with Foreign Minister Abdullah bin Zayed and the United Arab Emirates Ambassador to the UK. I have also spoken to Deputy Foreign Minister Anwar Gargash, most recently on 23 November. We welcome the news of Mr Hedges' pardon. He has now returned to the UK and has reunited with his wife.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:15:33.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012414/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012414/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken in response to the conviction of Matthew Hedges.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012415","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>The Foreign Secretary has consistently raised Matthew Hedges' case at the highest levels including most recently with the Emirati Foreign Minister on 25 November, and the Crown Prince on 12 November. I also spoke to Emirati Deputy Foreign Minister Anwar Gargash about the case on 23 November. As the Foreign Secretary said, Foreign and Commonwealth Office staff worked incredibly hard to bring about a speedy resolution to Matthew's case. He has now returned to the UK and has reunited with his wife.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:16:42.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012415/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012415/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans his Department has to respond the conviction of Matthew Hedges.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012416","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>We keep all our travel advice, including for the United Arab Emirates, under constant review to ensure it reflects our assessment of the risk to British nationals. We do not update our travel advice in relation to the specific circumstances of every consular assistance case, but will do so if we assess that other British nationals travelling or living in the area may be affected. We encourage all British nationals to make use of our travel advice, alongside other sources of information available to them, to help them plan for a safe trip.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:18:09.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012416/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012416/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","United Arab Emirates: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment his Department has made of its travel advice to the United Arab Emirates.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012417","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>We keep all our travel advice, including for the United Arab Emirates, under constant review to ensure it reflects our assessment of the risk to British nationals. We do not update our travel advice in relation to the specific circumstances of every consular assistance case, but will do so if we assess that other British nationals travelling or living in the area may be affected. We encourage all British nationals to make use of our travel advice, alongside other sources of information available to them, to help them plan for a safe trip.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:19:25.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012417/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012417/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012417/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","United Arab Emirates: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what guidance his Department has provided to (a) universities and (b) academics in the light of Matthew Hedges’s conviction.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012418","Home Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>The UK takes a wide range of measures to maintain the security of the border and prevent migrants from entering the country illegally. We carry out 100% checks on passengers arriving on scheduled services at the border to identify any criminal, security and immigration concerns. Where we believe someone poses a risk, Border Force officers can and do refuse them entry.</p><p>Border Force works closely with domestic and international partners on an intelligence led approach to detecting and preventing unlawful maritime activity including attempts to enter the UK clandestinely, and uses a combination of cutters, radar and aerial surveillance to detect and stop small craft</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-11-30T12:50:27.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012418/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012418/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012418/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Undocumented Migrants: English Channel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what his Department's policy is on preventing illegal migrants from entering the UK via sea routes.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","194754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012419","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>Following the court hearing on Wednesday 21 November, the Foreign Secretary released a statement and discussed Matthew Hedges' case with Foreign Minister Abdullah bin Zayed and the United Arab Emirates Ambassador to the UK. I also spoke to Deputy Foreign Minister Anwar Gargash most recently on 23 November. We welcome the news of Mr Hedges' pardon. He has now returned to the UK and has reunited with his wife</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:20:34.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012419/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012419/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012419/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what contact and at what level the UK Government has made with its counterparts in the United Arab Emirates subsequent to Matthew Hedges's conviction.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012420","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>As the Foreign Secretary said on 22 November, we have a close partnership with the United Arab Emirates. We have been clear that we do not agree with the charges but we are grateful to the UAE for the effort that put into resolving the situtation.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-30T13:21:51.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012420/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012420/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-22","Matthew Hedges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment the Government has made of the effect on the UK's bilateral relations with the United Arab Emirates as a result of the treatment of Matthew Hedges in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","194595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012421","Home Office","false","2018-11-30","<p>Border Force does not routinely publish this level of data on clandestines.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","194751","2018-11-30T12:52:16.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012421/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012421/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012421/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Undocumented Migrants: English Channel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many illegal migrants stranded at sea have rescued by UK officials in the last 12 months; and what the cost has been to the public purse of such operations.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","194755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012422","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-27","<p>The UK continues to monitor the number of civilian casualties and displaced persons as a result of the recent violence in Ghazni and Uruzgan. The Afghan Security Forces have been in the lead for the security of the Afghan people since 2015 and owing to the Afghan Security Forces response, the situation in these two provinces is stabilising. The UK is committed to supporting the Afghan Security Forces to ensure their capability continues to improve in order to successfully protect all ethnic and religious groups in Afghanistan.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-11-27T15:41:48.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012422/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012422/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-22","Afghanistan: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contribution the UK mission to Afghanistan is making to the protection of Hazara civilians.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","194619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012423","Home Office","false","2018-11-27","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested.</p><p>However, statistics on the European Arrest Warrant (EAW) are published by the National Crime Agency each year.</p><p>These figures are published at: <a href="http://www.nationalcrimeagency.gov.uk/publications/european-arrest-warrant-statistics" target="_blank">http://www.nationalcrimeagency.gov.uk/publications/european-arrest-warrant-statistics</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-11-27T17:16:42.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012423/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012423/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","European Arrest Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many outstanding European Arrest Warrants there are in respect of (a) British citizens and (b) non-UK EU citizens accused of criminal offences in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","194756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012424","Home Office","false","2019-02-20","<p>We have launched a targeted communications campaign to maximise aware-ness and reassure EU citizens of our commitment to protect their rights and entitlements. Activity will increase as we progress through the phased roll out of the scheme.</p><p>Individuals will have sufficient time to apply for status before the end of the post-exit period.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-02-20T13:18:27.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012424/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012424/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the level of awareness among non-UK EU citizens living in the UK of the legal requirement to apply for Settled Status.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","194757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012425","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-27","<p>The Department does not receive applications for new medical schools. The General Medical Council has responsibility for the approval process for new medical schools.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2018-11-27T17:18:04.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012425/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012425/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-22","Medicine: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has received any applications from Merseyside to establish a new medical school in that region.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","194620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012426","Home Office","false","2019-02-26","<p>There are conclusive grounds to accept that the two people referred under the National Referral Mechanism for the identification of victims of trafficking, are both victims of modern day slavery.</p><p>One individual has been granted a period of discretionary leave. There are no reasons to believe that the other individual requires protection and/or assistance and therefore a grant of Discretionary Leave has not been made. <br>The individual was issued a residence card as a non-EEA national family member confirming their right to reside in accordance with EEA Treaty rights.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-02-26T15:24:36.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012426/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012426/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-22","Deportation: West Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 9 October 2018 to Question 174681 on deportation: West Africa, what the outcome was of the considerations taking place in relation to the two people who were referred under the National Referral Mechanism for the identification of victims of trafficking; and what type of status was granted to the individual who was a family member of an EEA national.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","194670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012427","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-11-30","<p>The answer to Question 190943 was published on 27 November 2018 and can be found on the parliamentary website.</p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-11-30T13:17:16.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012427/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012427/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-11-22","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to respond to Question 190943, tabled on 13 November 2018, by the hon. Member for Oxford West and Abingdon.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","194758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012428","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-27","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-11-27T14:51:54.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012428/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012428/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-11-22","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 19 November to Question 190945 on Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit what information his Department holds on non-disclosure agreements on issues relating to the UK leaving the EU with (a) companies, (b) industry bodies and (c) other organisations.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","194759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012429","Treasury","false","2018-11-27","<p>As I said in my previous answer, the Government continues to engage with a large number of stakeholders as part of the UK’s withdrawal from the EU, and the sensitive nature of some discussions means that NDAs are required to facilitate conversations that otherwise may not have been able to take place.</p><p> </p><p>This information is not held centrally by HMT and could not be provided without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-11-27T15:39:56.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012429/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012429/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-11-22","Treasury: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 21 November 2018 to Question 190947 on Treasury: Brexit, for what reasons the Answer did not specify the number of non-disclosure agreements his Department has with private sector organisations; and if he will allow information on (a) the number of and (b) which companies have entered non-disclosure agreements to be made available to all hon. Members.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","194760"
