"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012486","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-29","<p>The value of the Ministry of Defence (MOD) inventory is shown in Note 11 to the MOD Annual Report and Accounts which is published on gov.uk at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministry-of-defence-annual-report-and-accounts-2017-to-2018.</p><p>A detailed breakdown of obsolete equipment is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The MOD continually reviews inventory holdings and, where stock is identified as surplus and no longer in use or obsolete, there are a number of disposal options, including via the Defence Equipment Sales Authority.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-29T15:47:43.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012486/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012486/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-22","Defence Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the inventory of his Department is; and what proportion of that inventory is obsolete.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","194789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012487","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-29","<p>The Department does not set general targets for rail demand growth.</p><p> </p><p>Our latest forecasts for rail passenger demand were published in the 2017 High-level Output Specification: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/high-level-output-specification-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/high-level-output-specification-2017</a>. Network Rail’s latest proposed forecasts for rail freight are published here: https://cdn.networkrail.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Rail-freight-forecasts-final-report.pdf. Both sets of forecasts are for the final financial year of control period 6 (2023/24).</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2018-11-29T16:23:33.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012487/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012487/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-22","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what (a) targets and (b) forecasts his Department has made of rail (i) passenger and (ii) freight growth by 2030.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","194790"
