"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012491","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-27","<p>Based on our internal assessment, following the change in grant rates we expect sales of ultra low emission cars to continue at similar levels in 2019 to those seen this year.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-11-27T15:47:24.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012491/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012491/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-22","Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has made an assessment of the effect of reducing incentives for plug-in (a) hybrid and (b) electric cars on the number of purchases of those vehicles.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","194792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012492","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-27","<p>We will launch a public consultation on mandatory learning disability and autism training for National Health Service and social care staff in the new year. Officials have been working with people with lived experience of learning disabilities and autism in developing the consultation proposals.</p><p>We want to hear a range of views, including those from people with a learning disability or autism and their families, and in line with Cabinet Office principles on consultation, we will tailor the consultation to meet the needs and preferences of different groups, including the provision of consultation documents in alternative formats.</p><p>The consultation will consider the role of people with a learning disability or autism in the development and deployment of training as they can bring a unique and valuable perspective as users of health and care services.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","194794 ; 194796","2018-11-27T17:26:29.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012492/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1012492/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-22","Learning Disability: Health Services and Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, when the Government plans to launch the consultation on options for delivering mandatory learning disability training for all relevant NHS and social care staff.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","194793"
