"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011679","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-29","<p>Officials at our Embassy in Jakarta, including the Ambassador, visit Papua regularly. During these visits, they consistently press the Indonesian authorities to address legitimate concerns and ensure the sustainable and equitable development of the province. This includes access to healthcare.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-29T15:24:17.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011679/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011679/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-21","Papua: Measles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in Indonesia Government on vaccinations for measles in West Papua after an outbreak in that province killed at least 100 children in 2018.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","194240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011680","Department for Education","false","2018-11-26","<p>The Department does not hold information centrally on the number of pupils who have been officially taken off roll by schools. Local authorities have a duty to make arrangements to establish the identities of children of compulsory school age in their area who are not registered pupils at a school and are not otherwise receiving suitable education.</p><p>The law is clear that a pupil’s name can only be deleted from the admission register on the grounds prescribed in regulation 8 of the Education (Pupil Registration) (England) Regulations 2006 as amended. All schools must notify the local authority when a pupil’s name is to be deleted from the admission register under any of the grounds prescribed in regulation 8.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-11-26T17:11:56.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011680/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011680/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-11-21","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the number of children who have been off-rolled in each of the last two years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","194055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011681","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-26","<p>In the period March 2018 to August 2018*, the Parole Board conducted 3,890 hearings and 2,647 hearings were completed. In this time the Parole Board made 1,280 release directions (81 of them were released on papers).</p><p> </p><p>In the period September 2017 to March 2018, the Parole Board conducted 4,418 hearings and 3,041 hearings were completed. The Parole Board made 1,613 release directions (138 of them were released on papers).</p><p> </p><p>In the period January 2016 to January 2017, the Parole Board conducted 7,956 hearings and 5,674 hearings were completed. The Parole Board made 3,045 release directions (425 of them were released on papers).</p><p> </p><p>* data for 2018-19 is only currently available for the period April-August 2018</p><p>Public protection will always be our priority. In 16/17 and 17/18 the Ministry of Justice provided additional funding to enable the Parole Board to induct and train over 100 new members and to hear more cases each month.</p><p> </p><p>In October this year the Government secured a further £1.5 million for the Parole Board to boost its operational capacity.</p><p> </p><p>We are carrying out a full review of the Parole Board rules, which will build on the work we have already done to increase transparency and ensure victims are better supported.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","194242 ; 194243 ; 194244 ; 194245 ; 194246","2018-11-26T15:51:15.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011681/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1011681/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-11-21","Parole","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many directions for release were made by the Parole Board from March 2018 to September 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East"